---
/**
 * DemoCard.astro
 * Pure UI component for the WikiSure™ demo.
 *
 * Perspective:
 * - Platform Provider (Embedded Insurance)
 *
 * Rules:
 * - NO business logic
 * - NO API calls
 * - NO AI execution
 * - NO state outside the DOM
 *
 * Purpose:
 * - Explain WHAT happens
 * - Explain WHY it matters
 * - Create "aha" moments through clarity
 */
---

<style>
  .card {
    max-width: 980px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    background: white;
    border-radius: 18px;
    padding: 36px;
    box-shadow: 0 20px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  }

  h1 {
    margin: 0 0 8px 0;
    font-size: 28px;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: 32px;
    font-size: 20px;
  }

  .subtle {
    color: #6b7280;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    font-size: 15px;
  }

  .perspective {
    background: #f1f5f9;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  label {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  input, textarea {
    width: 100%;
    padding: 10px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: 1px solid #d1d5db;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  textarea {
    min-height: 120px;
  }

  .grid2 {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 14px;
    margin-top: 10px;
  }

  button {
    margin-top: 18px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border-radius: 10px;
    border: none;
    background: #2563eb;
    color: white;
    font-weight: 700;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 14px;
  }

  .hint {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #6b7280;
    margin-top: 12px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .explain {
    margin-top: 14px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #374151;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  #decision {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding: 18px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: #f9fafb;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
  }
</style>

<div class="card">
  <h1>WikiSure™ — Semantic Governance Demo</h1>

  <p class="subtle">
    This demo shows how a <strong>platform provider</strong> can govern insurance
    definitions across partners, insurers and regulators — with AI support and
    human-in-the-loop control.
  </p>

  <div class="perspective">
    <strong>Perspective:</strong><br />
    You are a <strong>Platform Provider</strong> embedding insurance into your product.
    Your challenge is not pricing or APIs — it is <em>shared meaning</em>.
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 1 -->
  <h2>1. Define a Shared Term</h2>

  <label>Insurance Term</label>
  <input id="term" placeholder="e.g. Embedded Insurance Coverage Scope" />

  <div class="explain">
    Platforms work with insurers, MGAs, regulators and partners.
    If everyone uses the same word differently, integration slows down or breaks.
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 2 -->
  <h2>2. Compare Definitions</h2>

  <div class="grid2">
    <div>
      <label>Canonical Definition (Current Baseline)</label>
      <textarea
        id="canonical"
        placeholder="The currently agreed definition used across the ecosystem"
      ></textarea>
    </div>

    <div>
      <label>Proposed Change (Draft)</label>
      <textarea
        id="draft"
        placeholder="A proposed adjustment by a partner or insurer"
      ></textarea>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="explain">
    Changes often come from new regulations, new markets, or new distribution models.
    The question is not <em>who is right</em> — but whether the change is
    <strong>acceptable, traceable and aligned</strong>.
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 3 -->
  <h2>3. Governance & AI Assistance</h2>

  <button id="aiSuggestBtn">Show AI-Based Suggestion (Demo)</button>

  <div class="hint">
    In production, AI can suggest improvements, highlight conflicts or missing context.
    Humans remain fully in control and make the final decision.
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 4 -->
  <h2>4. Governance Decision</h2>

  <button id="governanceBtn">Run Governance Check</button>

  <div id="decision">
    <strong>Governance Outcome (Illustrative):</strong>
    <div class="explain">
      The proposed definition is acceptable <em>with conditions</em>.
      Required actions may include documentation updates, partner alignment or
      regulatory review.
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FINAL AHA -->
  <h2>Why this matters</h2>

  <div class="explain">
    WikiSure™ does not replace insurers, platforms or regulators.
    It provides a <strong>shared semantic layer</strong> that reduces friction,
    prevents misunderstandings and makes AI usable in regulated environments.
  </div>
</div>
